# GIS Toolbox — project rules

## Stack

- Static site: `index.html` loads ES module entry `js/app.js`.
- No npm/build pipeline in-repo; do not introduce one unless explicitly requested.
- Map: MapLibre (CDN in HTML). GIS workflows, import/export, and a visual pipeline editor live under `js/`.

## Where to change what

- App bootstrap and global UI wiring: `js/app.js` (large file — search for feature-specific handlers before adding sprawling logic).
- Shared state and layers: `js/core/state.js`, `js/core/data-model.js`.
- New import/export formats: `js/import/` or `js/export/` plus registration in the importer/exporter entry modules.
- Pipeline nodes: `js/workflow/nodes/` and related palette/engine files.
- Styling: `css/`; mobile behavior also uses `css/mobile.css` and responsive patterns in JS.

## Quality bar

- Preserve existing error handling (`handleError`, toasts, logger).
- Match surrounding code style (semicolons, quote style, comment density).
- After map or import/export changes, sanity-check in a browser via a local static server (`python3 -m http.server` from repo root).
